@startuml sequence_weather_flow
' Sequenz: Wetterdaten live laden, speichern, DB laden

actor User
participant UI as "Angular WeatherComponent"
participant FService as "Frontend WeatherService"
participant API as ".NET WeatherController"
participant Domain as "Domain WeatherService"
participant Repo as "WeatherRepository"
database DB as "SQLite"
participant Ext as "OpenMeteo API"

== Live Laden ==
User -> UI: Klick "Show Live OpenMeteo Data"
UI -> FService: getWeather()
FService -> API: GET /api/v1/weather/live
API -> Domain: GetLiveWeather()
Domain -> Ext: Request forecast
Ext --> Domain: JSON Data
Domain --> API: DTO[]
API --> FService: 200 OK + Data
FService --> UI: Observable emit()
UI -> User: Tabelle aktualisiert

== Speichern ==
User -> UI: Klick "Save Current Data"
UI -> API: POST /api/v1/weather/save
API -> Domain: SaveWeather()
Domain -> Repo: persist(data)
Repo -> DB: INSERT
DB --> Repo: Success
Repo --> Domain: OK
Domain --> API: Result
API --> UI: 200 OK (Saved)

== Laden aus DB ==
User -> UI: Klick "Show Saved Database Data"
UI -> FService: getWeatherFromDatabase()
FService -> API: GET /api/v1/weather/db
API -> Repo: Query data
Repo -> DB: SELECT
DB --> Repo: Rows
Repo --> API: Entities
API --> FService: 200 OK
FService --> UI: emit(rows)
UI -> User: Tabelle zeigt DB Daten
@enduml